'''Rayc Ryjerd''' was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] and the son of the [[Merchant/Legends|trader]] [[Rycar Ryjerd/Legends|Rycar Ryjerd]]. He was considered to be even more of an idiot than his [[Parent/Legends|father]]. By [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], he had accumulated debts and began working for the [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt]] in an effort to pay them off. Ryjerd was present in [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] that [[Standard year/Legends|year]] when the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] [[Siege of Jabba's Palace|arrived]] in order to bargain for the life of his friend [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], and he was aboard Jabba's [[Luxury-class sail barge|luxury sail barge]], the [[Khetanna/Legends|''Khetanna'']], when Jabba brought Skywalker and Solo to the [[Great Pit of Carkoon/Legends|Great Pit of Carkoon]] to be [[Death/Legends|executed]].

==Biography==
The [[Gender/Legends|male]] Rayc Ryjerd<ref name="card" /> was born before [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]]<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> to the [[Bimm/Legends|Bimm]] [[Merchant/Legends|trader]]<ref name="dadcard">{{CCG|set=Premiere Limited|cardname=Rycar Ryjerd}}</ref> [[Rycar Ryjerd/Legends|Rycar Ryjerd]]. While working as a [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]], he fell into debt after purchasing a [[Rayc Ryjerd's starship|starship]] and began working for<ref name="card" /> the [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]]<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|130|Jabba the Hutt (Jabba Desilijic Tiure)}}</ref> [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt]] in an effort to pay off his debts.<ref name="card" />

[[File:Rayc-ryjerd.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Ryjerd on Jabba's sail barge]]
By 4 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]],<ref name="NEC" /> Ryjerd had become romantically involved with the [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] gunrunner [[Laudica]], who dated him against her better judgment.<ref name="여자친구">{{CCG|set=Jabba's Palace Limited|cardname=Laudica}}</ref> Both of them were present in the courtroom of [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] in 4 ABY when the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] [[Rescue of Han Solo/Legends|arrived]] in order to [[Siege of Jabba's Palace|bargain]] for the life of his friend [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], who was being held [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoner]] in the palace's [[Prison/Legends|dungeons]]. When Jabba dropped Skywalker into the palace's [[Rancor/Legends|Rancor]] pit, Ryjerd and various other courtroom denizens watched from above as the Jedi did battle with [[Jabba's rancor/Legends|Jabba's rancor]]. After Skywalker [[Death/Legends|killed]] the creature, Jabba sentenced Skywalker, Solo, and Solo's companion [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] to be thrown into Tatooine's [[Great Pit of Carkoon/Legends|Great Pit of Carkoon]], where they would be eaten by a [[Sarlacc/Legends|Sarlacc]].<ref name="rotj" />

The [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] brought many members of his court onto the [[Khetanna/Legends|''Khetanna'']], a [[Luxury-class sail barge|luxury sail barge]], for the journey to the pit across the [[Dune Sea/Legends|Dune Sea]]. Ryjerd was one such court member. During the voyage, the drink-serving [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]] [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] spilled liquid on Ryjerd after being bumped into by the [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]]. When the ''Khetanna'' arrived at the Sarlacc pit, Skywalker and his friends made a [[Battle of the Great Pit of Carkoon|last stand]], and the ''Khetanna'' was destroyed.<ref name="rotj" />

==Personality and traits==
Ryjerd was a dishonest smuggler and was considered to be an idiot, even more so than his [[Parent/Legends|father]].<ref name="card" /> Although he was romantically involved with Laudica, she considered the arrangement to be contrary to her better judgment.<ref name="여자친구" /> Ryjerd sported a [[Hat/Legends|cap]] and had [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] and a mustache. He watched and jeered in delight when Skywalker battled Jabba's pet rancor.<ref name="rotj" />

==Behind the scenes==
Rayc Ryjerd first appeared as an extra in [[Richard Marquand]]'s [[1983]] film [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']], in which he was played by an uncredited actor.<ref name="rotj" /> The palace scenes were filmed between [[January 25]] and [[February 8]], [[1982]] on Stage 8 at [[Elstree Studios]], and the sail barge interior shots were filmed on Stage 9 between [[February 9]] and [[February 11]].<ref name="Making of">''[[The Making of Return of the Jedi]]''</ref> The ''[[Jabba's Palace Limited]]'' expansion set of the [[Decipher]] [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]], released in [[1998]], included a card of the character that gave him a name and biographical details,<ref name="card" /> with the name simultaneously being used on a separate card for Laudica.<ref name="여자친구" />

